issue.title: Plan
issue.body:
Plan

- [x] Support more types
- [x] Better output for sequence and map types for `inputs` and `outputs` methods

Blocked - https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/2746

- [x] `ModelMetadata` class
- [x] `model.end_profiling` method

Not doing (for now)

- [ ] `OnnxRuntime.device` method - not available for C API by design
- [ ] Backend API - probably not needed

Python API: https://microsoft.github.io/onnxruntime/python/api_summary.html

body:
Hi @ankane,

Thanks for the feature request. I think get_device() might be the only thing that needs to be given some thought. As I see it, get_device() in python returns a macro that is formed when the Py package is built (the macro is constructed based on the build options). We could have a similar logic for the C/C++ interface.

I don't see why the other 2 (Model metadata struct and the end_profiling() API) cannot be exposed right now either.

Thoughts @snnn @pranavsharma  ?

issue.title: Support a few new C/C++ APIs

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

body:
What about moving the GetAllProviders and GetAvailableProviders functions https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/python/onnxruntime_pybind_state.cc#L272
 into the main C API? That way the logic won't be duplicated between the different bindings (Ruby and python). This functionality does not exist in the Java API yet, but I think it would be useful. If this is a separate ticket, I can make one.
One idea was: people can add new execution provider without changing onnxruntime's existing code. So we can't provide functions like "GetAvailableProviders()" in our C API.

Hi @ankane 

Fetching the `ModelMetadata` and `end_profiling()`are supported via #2794 . I spoke to some folks and they say that the global method `get_device()` was apparently added only to support the onnx backend API (https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/master/onnx/backend/base.py) and is Python only. I think what you may have bee interested in is something along the lines of the `GetAvailableProviders()` in the C API and as @snnn mentions there are plans to support adding new execution provider with changing onnxruntime's existing code and hence supporting that API may not be the right way forward now. 

Please let me know if I can close this issue after the PR is merged. Thanks!

Thanks @hariharans29, #2794 looks great!

Re `get_device()`: thanks for the context. It sounds like `GetAvailableProviders()` will return similar info, and it's also used to determine fallback providers in Python. There's also `GetRegisteredProviderTypes()` which is used to implement the `get_providers()` method on `onnxruntime.InferenceSession`.

Totally understand if there are concerns with exposing provider APIs. Happy that model metadata and the profiling path are available.
Thanks @hariharans29! Is there a way to get the keys for `ModelMetadataLookupCustomMetadataMap`?
Also, fwiw, the Ruby library has been updated with these changes, as well as the other C API changes

Thanks @ankane. 

Whoops - maybe the API to get the keys should have been added along with my change :(. My bad. 

I can add the API in the next version if the API.
